                            <%# Use the class styled in style.css %>
                                <p>Basic steps for kitchen composting based on typical hotel procedures. <strong>Always verify hotel-specific details.</strong></p>

                                <%# Step 1 %>
                                    <div class="head" style="border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                                        <%# Use .head for icon/title styling %>
                                            <i class='bx bx-collection' style="color: var(--orange);"></i>
                                            <%# Icon for Collection %>
                                                <h2>1. Collect Organic Scraps</h2>
                                    </div>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Use designated, clean kitchen compost bins.</li>
                                        <li>Collect fruit/vegetable peels, cores, cuttings.</li>
                                        <li>Include coffee grounds, paper filters, tea bags (check for staples/plastic).</li>
                                        <li>Include eggshells.</li>
                                        <li><b>Avoid:</b> Meat, dairy, bones, oils/fats, diseased plants, non-organic materials (like plastic, metal, glass).</li>
                                    </ul>

                                    <%# Step 2 %>
                                        <div class="head" style="border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">
                                            <i class='bx bxs-truck' style="color: var(--blue);"></i>
                                            <%# Icon for Transfer %>
                                                <h2>2. Transfer to Main Compost Area</h2>
                                        </div>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Regularly empty kitchen bins into the hotel's main compost collection point (e.g., outdoor bin, designated third-party pickup area).</li>
                                            <li>Follow procedures for securing the main bin/area to prevent pests and odors.</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <%# Step 3 %>
                                            <div class="head" style="border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">
                                                <i class='bx bx-recycle' style="color: var(--green);"></i>
                                                <%# Icon for Balancing %>
                                                    <h2>3. Balancing Browns and Greens (If managing onsite bin)</h2>
                                            </div>
                                            <p><i>(This section applies <strong>only</strong> if the hotel manages its own active compost pile/bin. Ask your supervisor if unsure).</i></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Compost needs a mix of "Greens" (nitrogen-rich: food scraps) and "Browns" (carbon-rich: dried leaves, cardboard scraps, sawdust).</li>
                                                <li>Aim for roughly 2-3 parts Browns to 1 part Greens by volume for optimal decomposition.</li>
                                                <li>Layer materials or mix them gently when adding to the pile/bin.</li>
                                                <li>Maintain moisture: The pile should feel like a damp sponge, not soaking wet or bone dry. Add water if dry, or more browns if wet.</li>
                                                <li>Aerate the pile occasionally (e.g., turn with a pitchfork every 1-2 weeks) to provide oxygen, if managing an active bin.</li>
                                            </ul>

                                            <%# Step 4 %>
                                                <div class="head" style="border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">
                                                    <i class='bx bx-calendar-check' style="color: var(--yellow);"></i>
                                                    <%# Icon for Schedule %>
                                                        <h2>4. Follow Hotel Pickup/Processing Schedule</h2>
                                                </div>
                                                <ul>
                                                    <li>Ensure compostable waste is collected and stored according to the schedule and procedures provided by the hotel or its waste management partner.</li>
                                                    <li>Use only designated bins or bags as instructed.</li>
                                                </ul>

                                                <%# Step 5 %>
                                                    <div class="head" style="border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">
                                                        <i class='bx bx-message-alt-error' style="color: var(--red);"></i>
                                                        <%# Icon for Reminders %>
                                                            <h2>Key Reminders</h2>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <ul>
                                                        <li>Clean collection bins frequently to prevent odors and pests.</li>
                                                        <li>Always adhere to the specific composting guidelines provided by hotel management.</li>
                                                        <li><b>When in doubt about an item, put it in the general waste bin</b> to avoid contamination.</li>
                                                    </ul>

